WEBVTT

00:00.793 --> 00:02.503
[♪ opening theme song playing]

01:33.635 --> 01:35.303
Domain Expansion.

01:35.345 --> 01:36.889
Deadly Sentencing.

01:37.890 --> 01:38.933
[YUJI] A domain?

01:39.641 --> 01:41.769
Before he can activate
his technique,

01:42.101 --> 01:43.520
I have to beat him.

01:44.646 --> 01:47.649
[panting]

01:51.779 --> 01:53.363
[straining]

01:53.405 --> 01:55.198
Sorry, but all acts of violence

01:55.240 --> 01:57.743
are indefinitely prohibited
in this space.

01:58.077 --> 02:00.537
- For both of us.
- Both of us?

02:01.162 --> 02:02.330
[gasps]

02:04.499 --> 02:08.045
However, harmful remarks
are the exception.

02:09.088 --> 02:10.213
Judgeman,

02:10.589 --> 02:11.715
please begin.

02:11.757 --> 02:13.216
[♪ tense music playing]

02:15.260 --> 02:17.387
The defendant Yuji Itadori

02:17.429 --> 02:20.682
stands accused of committing
the following crime.

02:20.724 --> 02:24.019
On July 16th, 2017,
the defendant entered

02:24.061 --> 02:27.982
Maji Vegas pachinko parlor,
Sendai City, Miyagi Prefecture,

02:28.023 --> 02:31.068
despite being under
the legal age of 18 at the time.

02:31.568 --> 02:32.611
Huh?

02:33.528 --> 02:34.529
Oh!

02:34.571 --> 02:38.450
[stammering]

02:38.492 --> 02:39.743
Within this domain,

02:39.785 --> 02:41.369
Judgeman knows
all who've entered

02:41.411 --> 02:42.496
and everything they've done.

02:43.413 --> 02:45.373
But don't worry yourself
too much.

02:45.415 --> 02:48.167
That information
has never been shared with me.

02:48.209 --> 02:49.753
The verdict will be decided

02:49.795 --> 02:52.380
solely by the arguments
we present today.

02:53.256 --> 02:55.634
With the exception
of this evidence.

02:56.551 --> 02:57.552
Huh?

02:57.970 --> 02:59.471
Where'd you get that from?!

02:59.805 --> 03:02.057
This is the evidence
Judgeman provided

03:02.099 --> 03:03.475
and submitted for this case.

03:03.809 --> 03:05.936
There is no guarantee
that this will confirm

03:05.978 --> 03:08.022
the charges alleged
against you today.

03:08.522 --> 03:11.190
Nevertheless,
it will remain a secret to you.

03:11.232 --> 03:13.777
Knowing that, you must
now present your argument.

03:14.235 --> 03:16.113
Your goal is to clear suspicion

03:16.155 --> 03:18.782
and win an innocent verdict
from Judgeman.

03:20.199 --> 03:22.036
[YUJI] A court trial technique?

03:24.663 --> 03:25.789
That badge.

03:26.040 --> 03:28.042
So he really
was a defense lawyer.

03:28.416 --> 03:31.045
But isn't he acting
like a prosecutor here?

03:31.712 --> 03:33.797
Higuruma is a modern sorcerer.

03:33.839 --> 03:36.591
This domain is like
what Tengen talked about.

03:38.010 --> 03:41.638
Domains used to be a much more
standard skill set for sorcerers

03:41.680 --> 03:44.141
to use against their enemies
in the past.

03:45.142 --> 03:48.020
That's because they lacked
the guaranteed "kill element"

03:48.062 --> 03:50.022
that applies to today's attacks.

03:50.064 --> 03:53.150
Modern domains have become
guaranteed to be deadlier.

03:54.109 --> 03:56.277
The guarantee was
that users' techniques would,

03:56.319 --> 03:59.406
without question, hit
their target within the domain.

03:59.698 --> 04:01.825
That used to be
the commonplace function

04:01.867 --> 04:03.577
of domains in the past.

04:03.994 --> 04:07.081
By focusing too hard
on the "guaranteed kill" aspect,

04:07.122 --> 04:08.540
sorcerers raised the bar

04:08.582 --> 04:10.751
on requirements
for constructing a domain,

04:10.792 --> 04:13.212
making it
a more advanced skill,

04:13.628 --> 04:15.964
with fewer practitioners
every day.

04:16.840 --> 04:20.343
[YUJI] That means
this domain is founded on pacts.

04:20.385 --> 04:22.137
It prevents lethal use,

04:22.179 --> 04:23.805
prohibits physical harm and...

04:24.263 --> 04:26.767
it requires some explanation
of its rules.

04:29.728 --> 04:32.189
[HIGURUMA] You get one chance
to make a statement.

04:32.231 --> 04:33.899
The same goes for me.

04:34.399 --> 04:35.734
After your statement,

04:35.776 --> 04:39.362
I will get to make my rebuttal
using this evidence.

04:39.404 --> 04:42.323
And then, Judgeman will
announce his verdict

04:42.365 --> 04:44.993
in accordance
with the Six Codes.

04:45.827 --> 04:47.662
[YUJI] What happens
if I'm found guilty?

04:48.080 --> 04:50.457
Unfortunately,
I am under no obligation

04:50.498 --> 04:51.708
to answer that question.

04:51.750 --> 04:53.752
But I will
at least tell you this.

04:54.128 --> 04:55.796
After all, you have rights.

04:56.797 --> 04:59.007
If guilty,
you have three options.

04:59.549 --> 05:02.219
Silence, confession, or denial.

05:02.636 --> 05:05.264
Your denial may
include false statements.

05:06.807 --> 05:08.267
You mean I can lie?

05:08.725 --> 05:10.269
In a court of law?

05:10.769 --> 05:12.896
If everyone told the truth
in court,

05:13.272 --> 05:15.440
there would be no need
for trials.

05:16.858 --> 05:19.153
Now, make your argument.

05:19.194 --> 05:21.238
Judgeman is not very patient.

05:24.199 --> 05:26.660
[YUJI] I did go
to that pachinko parlor.

05:26.701 --> 05:28.620
And I totally played some games.

05:28.662 --> 05:30.122
Think I even won some.

05:30.664 --> 05:33.917
I can't avoid lying if I still
wanna claim my innocence.

05:34.293 --> 05:35.669
So naturally,

05:35.710 --> 05:37.336
what I need to consider is

05:37.629 --> 05:39.380
what could be
in that evidence.

05:40.423 --> 05:42.592
[HIGURUMA] There is no guarantee
that this will confirm

05:42.634 --> 05:45.179
the charges alleged
against you today.

05:46.096 --> 05:48.347
[YUJI] One, if that evidence
doesn't prove I entered

05:48.389 --> 05:49.641
the pachinko parlor,

05:49.683 --> 05:52.351
I just need to deny it
or remain silent.

05:52.393 --> 05:53.728
No!

05:53.854 --> 05:56.731
Two, if the evidence only
proves I entered the parlor,

05:56.773 --> 05:58.859
can I say it was
for another reason?

05:58.900 --> 06:00.694
I just went in
to use their bathroom.

06:00.735 --> 06:03.280
But if the evidence
turns out to be a bust,

06:03.322 --> 06:04.823
then I might be
digging my own grave

06:04.865 --> 06:07.201
by admitting I definitely
entered the parlor.

06:07.993 --> 06:11.079
Three, if the evidence proves
I not only entered the parlor

06:11.121 --> 06:14.333
but also played the games,
I'm basically screwed.

06:14.875 --> 06:16.126
I regret it!

06:16.251 --> 06:18.545
But what if confessing
lightens my sentence?

06:19.004 --> 06:22.007
Wait, does this court even
offer lighter punishments?

06:23.842 --> 06:25.177
I confess.

06:25.927 --> 06:28.722
The fact is I entered
the pachinko parlor,

06:28.763 --> 06:31.141
but it was only
because I needed to poop.

06:31.183 --> 06:32.934
And I had to use
their bathroom.

06:34.186 --> 06:35.394
[HIGURUMA] Is that so?

06:35.770 --> 06:37.396
[YUJI]
I'm going with option two.

06:37.438 --> 06:38.773
I don't know
if this court accepts

06:38.815 --> 06:40.525
extenuating circumstances,

06:40.567 --> 06:42.819
but this excuse
is the most relatable.

06:43.653 --> 06:45.072
Let's hope.

06:45.404 --> 06:47.157
[HIGURUMA] Now, it's my turn.

06:47.199 --> 06:48.992
Let's take a look
at the evidence.

06:51.828 --> 06:53.496
This is security camera footage,

06:53.538 --> 06:56.041
from the antique shop
near Maji Vegas.

06:56.083 --> 06:57.209
Huh?

06:57.251 --> 06:58.626
The store has an ATM

06:58.668 --> 07:01.171
which captured this image
on the day in question.

07:02.923 --> 07:04.925
Uh...

07:04.966 --> 07:07.010
Note how striking
the resemblance.

07:07.052 --> 07:10.429
Both face and build are
a perfect match to Yuji Itadori.

07:11.472 --> 07:13.767
Uh... [chuckles]

07:14.309 --> 07:17.062
[HIGURUMA] And since he just
admitted to entering the parlor,

07:17.104 --> 07:19.106
this photo makes it clear
that his excuse

07:19.147 --> 07:20.439
about needing the bathroom

07:20.481 --> 07:22.567
isn't worth a roll
of toilet paper.

07:23.068 --> 07:25.904
One can thus reason
that despite being underage,

07:25.946 --> 07:27.446
Itadori entered the parlor

07:27.488 --> 07:29.366
with the intent
to play pachinko.

07:29.908 --> 07:31.534
So then you're saying

07:31.910 --> 07:33.120
that's a crime?

07:33.578 --> 07:35.663
The parlor had
clear posted signs

07:35.705 --> 07:38.750
explicitly prohibiting minors
from entering the premises.

07:39.293 --> 07:41.378
You are charged
with criminal trespassing.

07:41.669 --> 07:43.713
Article 130 of the Penal Code,

07:43.755 --> 07:47.175
the "Businesses affecting
Public Morals Regulation Act."

07:47.217 --> 07:48.969
But it doesn't punish minors.

07:49.761 --> 07:51.721
No fair. You set me up.

07:51.763 --> 07:54.182
There was no way
for me to talk my way out of it.

07:54.224 --> 07:56.017
Should I have gone
with option three?

07:56.059 --> 07:57.852
What are you talking about?

07:57.894 --> 07:59.646
Japan prohibits gambling,

07:59.687 --> 08:03.066
so parlors and ATMs
are separate legal entities.

08:03.650 --> 08:06.527
Sometimes multiple parlors
even share ATMs.

08:06.569 --> 08:09.781
You were only on trial
for entering into Maji Vegas.

08:09.823 --> 08:11.408
All you needed to say was,

08:11.450 --> 08:14.911
"I'm sorry, but I don't
recognize that parlor."

08:14.953 --> 08:16.621
And that way,
you can deny the charge

08:16.663 --> 08:18.081
without lying to me.

08:18.999 --> 08:21.335
Wait, we haven't heard
the verdict yet.

08:22.836 --> 08:24.045
[gavel banging]

08:27.757 --> 08:29.050
Guilty.

08:29.092 --> 08:30.593
Confiscation.

08:33.680 --> 08:35.390
[YUJI] We're back
where we started?

08:35.807 --> 08:37.600
Now I've been declared guilty.

08:37.642 --> 08:39.269
I don't feel any different.

08:39.311 --> 08:40.479
- [gavel whirring]
- [gasps]

08:40.519 --> 08:41.855
[♪ rock music playing]

08:48.862 --> 08:50.155
His gavel!

08:54.117 --> 08:55.576
What a weapon.

08:55.618 --> 08:58.455
Not only can he make it appear
and disappear at will,

08:58.497 --> 09:00.539
he can alter its size too?

09:01.124 --> 09:02.917
Wait, something's wrong.

09:04.002 --> 09:05.420
You're pretty tough.

09:06.087 --> 09:08.215
At least I still have that.

09:11.259 --> 09:13.594
Because I can't control
my cursed energy!

09:20.894 --> 09:22.145
[gavel banging]

09:22.187 --> 09:24.772
[NARRATOR]
Law apprenticeship period 59.

09:24.814 --> 09:28.026
Iwate Bar Association's
Hiromi Higuruma.

09:28.068 --> 09:29.694
Age 36.

09:30.862 --> 09:32.822
He easily cleared all obstacles,

09:32.864 --> 09:34.074
like the entry exam

09:34.115 --> 09:36.451
to Tokyo University's
School of Law,

09:36.493 --> 09:37.576
and the old bar exam

09:37.994 --> 09:40.414
that preceded the institution
of the law school system.

09:41.206 --> 09:42.249
To Higuruma,

09:42.290 --> 09:43.958
it was all a matter of simply

09:44.000 --> 09:46.545
inputting and outputting
the necessary knowledge

09:46.585 --> 09:48.796
that was needed
for each individual task

09:48.838 --> 09:49.881
in front of him.

09:50.589 --> 09:53.801
[NARRATOR] His peers whispered
in the hallways behind his back

09:53.843 --> 09:56.137
that he was a genius
of some kind.

09:56.179 --> 09:57.180
And yet,

09:57.680 --> 10:00.392
the gem that shone brightest
from his unlimited potential

10:00.434 --> 10:03.978
was his overwhelming talent
as a jujutsu sorcerer.

10:04.020 --> 10:06.147
[Yuji grunting]

10:06.189 --> 10:08.942
His technique came
with his domain by default.

10:08.983 --> 10:10.818
But through analyzing
his domain,

10:10.860 --> 10:13.947
he also learned the fundamentals
of how barriers work.

10:13.988 --> 10:15.407
- [crashes]
- [Yuji grunts]

10:16.533 --> 10:18.952
[NARRATOR] Then, working
backwards from barriers,

10:18.993 --> 10:21.913
he intuitively gathered how
to manipulate cursed energy

10:21.955 --> 10:23.415
for physical enhancement.

10:23.457 --> 10:26.251
And within 12 days
of awakening as a sorcerer,

10:26.293 --> 10:29.588
his powers had grown
to match those of a Grade One.

10:29.963 --> 10:31.506
Before entering the colony,

10:31.548 --> 10:34.509
Higuruma exorcised
many cursed spirits.

10:34.551 --> 10:36.553
And he struck down
over 20 players

10:36.595 --> 10:39.389
who had the misfortune
of attacking him first.

10:48.398 --> 10:50.442
[panting]

11:17.218 --> 11:19.804
You lost the ability
to control cursed energy?

11:20.555 --> 11:22.223
[YUJI] Didn't you
take it from me?

11:23.766 --> 11:25.560
[HIGURUMA]
The penalty of Confiscation

11:25.602 --> 11:29.189
makes it temporarily impossible
to use one's curse technique.

11:29.814 --> 11:32.066
So I'm guessing you've
never had a cursed technique

11:32.108 --> 11:33.401
to begin with?

11:34.068 --> 11:35.736
That must be why the penalty

11:35.778 --> 11:38.365
switched to blocking
the use of cursed energy.

11:39.157 --> 11:41.742
Coincidentally,
Confiscation is generally

11:41.784 --> 11:44.787
a supplementary sentence
never imposed on its own.

11:45.288 --> 11:48.124
It's terrifying to think
about how good he is.

11:49.292 --> 11:51.294
How can he hold
his own against me

11:51.336 --> 11:52.504
without cursed energy?

11:53.380 --> 11:55.882
He's using his natural
physical prowess,

11:55.923 --> 11:57.884
not his might as a sorcerer.

11:57.925 --> 12:00.887
He must have incredibly high
physical durability.

12:00.928 --> 12:03.806
When sorcerers lose the use
of their technique,

12:03.848 --> 12:06.685
they often struggle with basic
cursed energy control.

12:07.726 --> 12:11.064
Their instincts probably dull
over the many long years.

12:11.105 --> 12:13.483
But the complete inability
to use cursed energy

12:13.525 --> 12:15.360
is even more disadvantageous.

12:15.402 --> 12:18.572
Yet he can still fight this well
under these circumstances.

12:18.613 --> 12:20.948
My first strike would have
usually settled the battle

12:20.990 --> 12:22.409
against most foes.

12:23.326 --> 12:25.870
If I'm not careful,
he'll trip me up.

12:26.745 --> 12:29.123
I'll crush him
with my full might.

12:34.795 --> 12:35.880
[gasps]

12:35.922 --> 12:37.257
[creaking]

12:39.593 --> 12:40.635
[grunts]

12:52.397 --> 12:53.523
[grunts]

12:59.320 --> 13:00.363
[grunts]

13:06.077 --> 13:07.036
[gasps]

13:07.078 --> 13:09.289
[grunting]

13:09.664 --> 13:11.165
[HIGURUMA] You're incredible!

13:11.207 --> 13:14.210
It's like I'm fighting some kind
of unbreakable doll.

13:14.252 --> 13:16.713
[YUJI] Shit, shit, shit, shit!

13:16.755 --> 13:18.172
How long will this last?

13:18.214 --> 13:19.840
I need my cursed energy.

13:19.882 --> 13:21.134
Come back to me!

13:21.468 --> 13:23.303
He's got such a strong ability.

13:23.344 --> 13:25.012
There must be
something I could do.

13:25.388 --> 13:28.015
Something that puts Higuruma
at a disadvantage.

13:28.516 --> 13:29.559
Think.

13:29.601 --> 13:31.102
Think, think!

13:31.810 --> 13:33.563
A technique for court trials.

13:34.188 --> 13:35.523
Trials.

13:42.196 --> 13:44.198
[gasps] Higuruma!

13:44.616 --> 13:46.576
I want a retrial!

13:46.618 --> 13:49.537
[panting]

13:56.419 --> 13:57.878
You figured it out.

13:57.920 --> 13:59.714
[panting] That...

13:59.756 --> 14:01.758
That was... That was close.

14:01.800 --> 14:04.427
I... I get
a second trial, right?

14:05.219 --> 14:07.013
[NARRATOR] As long as
the targeted defendant

14:07.054 --> 14:09.140
never actually
admitted their guilt,

14:09.182 --> 14:11.559
even after having previously
been found guilty

14:11.601 --> 14:13.978
and subjected
to penalty by Judgeman,

14:14.020 --> 14:17.607
they are entitled
to demand up to two retrials.

14:17.649 --> 14:21.695
Judgeman is incapable
of refusing such a request.

14:23.822 --> 14:25.948
I demand a do-over!

14:28.827 --> 14:31.120
The court calls Yuji Itadori.

14:31.162 --> 14:34.207
You stand accused
of mass murder in Shibuya

14:34.248 --> 14:38.795
on the night of Halloween,
October 31st, 2018.

14:41.840 --> 14:42.799
Yeah.

14:42.841 --> 14:44.050
I killed all of them.

14:44.551 --> 14:45.844
I'm not going to deny it.

14:49.096 --> 14:50.682
Guilty!

14:50.724 --> 14:52.642
Confiscation!

14:52.684 --> 14:55.603
Death penalty!

14:59.399 --> 15:01.067
[YOSHIZAWA] Higuruma.

15:01.526 --> 15:03.611
[♪ gentle music playing]

15:06.656 --> 15:07.948
[HIGURUMA] Yoshizawa.

15:08.825 --> 15:10.493
I've already submitted
the proposal,

15:10.535 --> 15:12.119
if that's what
you're here about.

15:13.413 --> 15:15.665
No, I'm not here about that.

15:15.707 --> 15:17.417
I took a look at the documents.

15:17.458 --> 15:18.585
They're wonderful.

15:19.085 --> 15:22.463
Good enough as-is for the judge
to use in his sentencing.

15:23.922 --> 15:26.426
You wanted to be either
a public prosecutor

15:26.467 --> 15:28.595
or defense lawyer,
is that right?

15:29.220 --> 15:30.388
Yes.

15:30.805 --> 15:32.348
Consider something else.

15:33.307 --> 15:36.227
How would you feel
about becoming a judge instead?

15:45.361 --> 15:46.654
[NARRATOR] The heaviest sentence

15:46.696 --> 15:49.031
Judgeman can impose
on the guilty

15:49.490 --> 15:53.912
is Confiscation accompanied
by the death penalty.

15:55.830 --> 15:57.582
Confiscation
makes it impossible

15:57.624 --> 15:59.793
for the guilty party
to use their technique,

15:59.834 --> 16:03.003
or in Itadori's case,
control his cursed energy.

16:03.045 --> 16:04.297
As prosecutor,

16:04.338 --> 16:07.216
Higuruma is granted
the Executioner's Sword.

16:08.384 --> 16:11.345
Anyone cut
by the Executioner's Sword

16:11.721 --> 16:13.598
will without exception,

16:13.640 --> 16:16.183
meet their untimely death.

16:16.643 --> 16:20.020
[HIGURUMA] Being empathetic
to another person's feelings

16:20.062 --> 16:22.565
means understanding
their weakness.

16:23.357 --> 16:25.443
The weakness of victims.

16:25.485 --> 16:27.487
The weakness of criminals.

16:28.362 --> 16:30.949
Day after day after day.

16:31.950 --> 16:34.243
I was so fed up with everything.

16:34.911 --> 16:36.704
"So ugly."

16:36.746 --> 16:38.289
That's what I started to think

16:38.331 --> 16:41.375
every time I tried to help
someone who needed a break.

16:42.042 --> 16:44.170
Just like you, Itadori!

16:46.673 --> 16:49.467
All people are weak and ugly!

16:49.926 --> 16:53.346
No matter how much you long
for them to have noble souls!

16:55.890 --> 16:58.184
There's nothing for you
down that path!

16:58.225 --> 17:00.645
The darkness before you
is just that!

17:01.980 --> 17:03.857
Even if you shine a light on it,

17:04.357 --> 17:06.860
you'll just find
blinding nothingness!

17:06.901 --> 17:07.986
[Yuji grunts]

17:13.491 --> 17:14.701
I'm sorry.

17:15.117 --> 17:17.203
I don't want to become a judge.

17:18.913 --> 17:20.373
[grunts, inhales]

17:22.333 --> 17:23.584
[YOSHIZAWA] I see.

17:24.002 --> 17:26.044
May I ask why you feel this way?

17:26.963 --> 17:30.299
[HIGURUMA]
All people are weak and ugly.

17:32.426 --> 17:34.721
I'm not interested
in promotions,

17:34.762 --> 17:36.514
so I'm not cut out for it.

17:37.431 --> 17:38.599
However,

17:38.933 --> 17:40.100
at the time,

17:40.142 --> 17:41.936
at least up until that moment,

17:42.729 --> 17:45.023
I believed
that the very depravity

17:45.063 --> 17:47.025
which no other creatures
possessed

17:47.065 --> 17:48.818
was meant to be cherished!

17:49.318 --> 17:50.403
Why?

17:50.987 --> 17:52.405
Yuji Itadori!

17:52.989 --> 17:55.073
Why did you admit your guilt?

17:55.115 --> 17:57.284
[NARRATOR] The evidence
that Judgeman submits

17:57.326 --> 17:59.871
is shared with the sorcerer
before it is revealed

17:59.913 --> 18:02.582
to the defendant during
the course of the trial.

18:03.249 --> 18:05.334
[HIGURUMA] The evidence
Judgeman provided

18:05.376 --> 18:07.628
was about the demon
harbored inside you.

18:07.670 --> 18:08.880
Sukuna!

18:08.922 --> 18:10.715
You didn't kill them!

18:11.799 --> 18:14.052
So why? Why?

18:14.092 --> 18:15.302
[grunts]

18:15.344 --> 18:16.387
[grunts]

18:16.429 --> 18:17.805
[strains]

18:20.850 --> 18:22.060
[gasps]

18:22.100 --> 18:23.519
[groans]

18:28.190 --> 18:29.275
[Yuji grunts]

18:29.316 --> 18:30.818
[Higuruma groaning]

18:33.404 --> 18:34.655
Uh, hey.

18:36.198 --> 18:39.869
Penal Code,
Article 39, Clause One.

18:39.911 --> 18:42.580
Being deprived
of either sound judgment

18:42.622 --> 18:44.707
or control of one's actions

18:44.749 --> 18:47.543
qualifies as non compos mentis.

18:49.211 --> 18:50.797
That night in Shibuya,

18:50.838 --> 18:53.424
Sukuna took control
of your body, didn't he?

18:53.466 --> 18:55.384
How do you know about Sukuna?

18:56.094 --> 18:57.720
In other words,

18:57.762 --> 19:00.222
you lacked control
of your actions.

19:00.264 --> 19:03.434
You didn't voluntarily
surrender control either.

19:03.476 --> 19:04.769
And so,

19:05.143 --> 19:06.186
you're innocent.

19:08.606 --> 19:10.316
You've committed no crime.

19:12.359 --> 19:15.071
Regardless of all that,
it's still my fault.

19:15.863 --> 19:18.074
Because I was too weak
to stop him.

19:22.078 --> 19:23.454
I see.

19:24.204 --> 19:25.331
Higuruma,

19:25.832 --> 19:27.917
why did you release
your technique just now?

19:31.838 --> 19:33.965
I wanted to return to my roots.

19:35.591 --> 19:36.843
Itadori,

19:37.384 --> 19:39.177
there may still be
plenty of people

19:39.219 --> 19:41.179
who are weak and ugly like you,

19:41.221 --> 19:42.932
wandering around out there.

19:44.558 --> 19:47.269
Put your shirt back on
and have a seat.

19:47.311 --> 19:49.229
I'm giving you
my hundred points.

20:02.702 --> 20:03.911
Itadori?

20:03.953 --> 20:05.163
[YUJI] Hmm?

20:05.245 --> 20:07.040
Have you ever killed someone
by your own will,

20:07.081 --> 20:08.457
and not as Sukuna?

20:10.793 --> 20:11.836
[Yuji sighs]

20:16.132 --> 20:17.257
I have.

20:23.263 --> 20:24.640
I see.

20:26.100 --> 20:28.019
Didn't it feel awful?

20:29.227 --> 20:31.397
[♪ closing theme song playing]

21:59.819 --> 22:02.196
[HIGURUMA] Kogane,
add a new rule.

22:03.156 --> 22:06.533
Make possible the transfer
of points between players.

22:07.785 --> 22:10.663
Of course, this should count
toward the "change in points"

22:10.704 --> 22:12.330
mentioned in Rule Number Eight.

22:12.748 --> 22:14.374
Approved. Rule added.

22:14.750 --> 22:16.002
Rule Number Ten.

22:16.085 --> 22:18.336
Players are able
to transfer a number of points

22:18.378 --> 22:21.048
of their choosing
to other players in the game.

22:21.090 --> 22:22.466
[sighs in relief]

22:22.508 --> 22:25.594
[HIGURUMA] Kogane, give
one of my points to Itadori.

22:26.095 --> 22:27.513
[KOGANE] As you wish.

22:28.097 --> 22:29.056
Huh?

22:29.598 --> 22:33.144
You have been granted
one point by Hiromi Higuruma.

22:33.811 --> 22:35.562
[HIGURUMA] Now neither of us
will have to worry

22:35.604 --> 22:38.691
about our techniques
being stripped for 19 days.

22:39.441 --> 22:40.734
Take care.

22:41.110 --> 22:42.528
[YUJI] Higuruma!

22:42.569 --> 22:44.155
What are you planning to do now?

22:44.697 --> 22:46.240
You could join us if you want.

22:46.282 --> 22:47.992
We'd be stronger with your help.

22:49.535 --> 22:51.162
[HIGURUMA]
My two remaining points

22:51.537 --> 22:53.998
are from the judge
and prosecutor

22:54.040 --> 22:56.334
that I killed
before coming to Tokyo.

22:56.834 --> 22:58.627
Once the barriers open up,

22:59.045 --> 23:00.838
I think I might turn myself in.

23:01.255 --> 23:04.591
Until then, I'll think about
what I should do next.

23:05.218 --> 23:07.803
Besides, if I stay with you,

23:07.845 --> 23:10.181
I'm likely
to hate myself even more.

23:11.307 --> 23:12.432
Sorry.

23:12.474 --> 23:13.976
I'm not criticizing you.

23:15.728 --> 23:16.937
See you later.

23:20.191 --> 23:21.483
[door closes]

23:25.654 --> 23:27.323
[MEGUMI] A new rule
will be added soon.

23:27.365 --> 23:28.949
[KOGANE] A number of points
of their choosing

23:28.991 --> 23:30.034
to other players.

23:30.117 --> 23:31.327
[REGGIE]
If you don't fight to kill...

23:31.369 --> 23:32.410
[MEGUMI] You're okay with this?!

23:32.745 --> 23:33.996
[TAKABA] I don't want you
as my Wi-Fi! [yells]

23:34.038 --> 23:35.706
[MEGUMI]
Hand over all your points.

23:35.748 --> 23:36.790
Do as I say.
